        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In modern web applications, extracting text from images or documents is a common requirement, but implementing robust OCR can be challenging. JavaScript developers often struggle with integrating accurate and efficient OCR solutions that scale in production, especially when dealing with varied document types and real-time demands. The Nanonets OCR S model, particularly the F16 variant, addresses this by offering high-accuracy text extraction with low latency, making it suitable for real-time applications. Its REST API is straightforward to integrate with JavaScript, whether in Node.js backends or browser-based frontends, reducing development overhead."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This post will walk you through setting up the Nanonets OCR S API in a JavaScript environment, provide detailed code examples in TypeScript, analyze performance characteristics, and discuss cost-effective deployment strategies. By the end, you'll have a concrete understanding of how to leverage this model for production-grade OCR in your services, complete with benchmarks and troubleshooting tips."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capabilities of Nanonets OCR S for JavaScript Developers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S is optimized for speed and accuracy, supporting multiple languages and document types, which is critical for diverse JavaScript applications. It can handle handwritten text, printed text, and various image formats, making it versatile for use cases like invoice processing, ID verification, or content digitization. The model's F16 variant balances precision and performance, achieving over 98% accuracy on standard benchmarks while maintaining low computational overhead."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key features for JavaScript developers include:"
          }
