      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Nanonets OCR S API accepts image URLs or base64-encoded files in the request body, returning a structured JSON response with extracted text and confidence scores. Understanding this structure is key to parsing results effectively in your JavaScript application."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A typical request includes the image source and optional parameters like page numbers for PDFs. The response contains a result array with predictions, each labeled with text, coordinates, and a score indicating confidence. For instance, a score above 0.9 suggests high reliability, which you can use to filter outputs in your code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h3",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Large Images and Errors"
          }
