        "type": "blockquote",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Note:",
            "bold": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Always set up billing alerts in the Nanonets dashboard and review your usage regularly. The API has rate limits (e.g., 10 requests per second by default), so plan your scaling accordingly to avoid throttling."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For large-scale deployments, estimate costs based on your expected request volume. For example, processing 100,000 images monthly would cost approximately $500, which is competitive compared to alternatives when factoring in accuracy and latency benefits."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Troubleshooting and Deployment Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common issues in production include authentication errors (HTTP 401), rate limiting (HTTP 429), and image format problems. To address these, validate API keys during startup, implement exponential backoff for retries, and preprocess images to ensure compatibility. Additionally, log errors with context, such as request IDs, to facilitate debugging."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For deployment, follow these best practices:"
          }
